title: Understanding Data Types
text: In computing, a 'data type' specifies the kind of data that can be stored and manipulated within a program. Common data types include numbers, text, and logical $$\frac{true}{false}$$.

title: Familiar Data Types
text:
Some familiar data types in many programming languages are:
- Integer (to store whole numbers)
- Float or double (to store decimal numbers)
- String (to store text)
- Boolean (to store $$ rac{true}{false}$$ values)

title: Start Date: An Unusual Data Type
text: While the concept of a 'start date' is often used in programming and databases, it is not a standard data type like integer or boolean. Instead, dates might be handled using specific libraries or as a $$\frac{string}{number}$$ type.
